  * source/compiler/harbour.sly
    ! Fixed minor bug with GetA and MACROTEXT (due to recent optimization of MACROTEXT)
      - Added new MacroText to encapsulate the optimization and make available in one more context.

    + Implemented few TODOs - Allowing xHarbour to compile:
      @ x,y GET &xMacro.Suffix -> Clipper complain -> Error C2081  Macro of declared symbol: '&CMACRO.1' (if cMacro is declared)
      @ x,y GET &( xMacro ) -> Clipper complain -> Error C2047  GET contains complex macro.
      @ x,y GET &( xMacro )[...] -> Clipper complain -> Error C2047  GET contains complex macro.

  * source/rtl/tget.prg
  * source/rtl/tgetlist.prg
    ! Fixed few compatibility problems:
      - Clipper is not erroring if Get value is Array or Block - it simply skips the Get.
      - Clipper skips a GET if the value of the get is NIL or "" (or Array or Block).
      - Clipper will correctly re-display and will allow editing of a var which was previosly NIL, or "", or Array, or Block
        once the value is reset to editable value.

  * tests/testget.prg
    + Added #ifdef __HARBOUR__ to protect sample code which Clipper can't compile.

  * tests/tstblock.prg
    + Added 1 comment.

