2002-01-19 06:11 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * source/compiler/harbour.slx
    ! Minor bug correction.

  * include/hbpcode.h
  * include/hbcomp.h
  * source/compiler/genc.c
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + Added support for HB_P_LOCALNEARADDINT, HB_P_LOCALNEARSETINT, HB_P_LEFT, HB_P_RIGHT*, HB_P_SUBSTR*
      /* HB_P_RIGHT & HB_P_SUBSTR are not completed yet. */

  * include/hbapi.h
  * source/vm/eval.c
  * source/vm/extend.c
  * source/vm/fastitem.c
  * source/vm/fm.c
  * source/vm/hvm.c
  * source/compiler/harbour.c
  * include/hbexprb.c
  * include/hbexprc.c
  * source/compiler/harbour.sly
  * source/compiler/hbfix.c
  * source/compiler/hbpcode.c
    * Enhanced string sharing and fast item technology, and optimized loops, := += -= ++ -- and Left().

  + tests/tstloop.prg
    + Added extensive loop speed testing.

/* xHarbour is now more than 400% faster than Harbour on most common code, and about 40% faster than Clipper on same.  */

     Here are the results for tests/tstloop.prg:

              Empty Loops    Eval()      :=      := +=      -=      Left()     Total
              -----------    ------    ------    -----    ------    ------    ------
  xHarbour:          7.71     32.07      9.02    13.79     11.11     19.72     93.47 Sec.
  Clippe  :         13.29     34.22     14.94    17.52     18.90     31.80    130.67 Sec.
  Harbour :         12.77     43.76     15.92    24.75     24.15    140.77    262.17 Sec.

  The above was for 10,000,000 loops for each operation on an 1Ghz Athlon Win XP using BCC 5.5.

  You can confirm those results by downloading BCC 5.5 bin distribution from http://www.Profit-Master/Downloads/xhb-bin-bcc.zip

  NOTE: FWH users *must* recompile ALL FWH PRG files!!!

*/

