  /* On my Athlon 1Ghz XP Notebook xHarbour is almost 10 times faster than Harbour on this Eval() speed test.

    Clipper :  4.17
    xHarbour:  4.30
    Harbour : 39.74 // Not a typo!

    Actual single Eval() is almost 4-5 times faster.
  */

2002-01-13 22:10 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  + tests/ppclass.ch
    + Added a Clipper compliant version of hbclass.ch (syntax relys on Harbour PP bugs)
      /* This is the file used to burn the internal support for #include "hbclass.ch". */

  * tests/pp.prg
    + Added -I description to -H switch.
    ! Corrected processing of repeatable groups.
      Clipper will repeat N times, based on the marker with the HIGHEST number of values in the given group.
      Clipper also allows a Repeatble Group to refernce a marker that is NON Optional. In such case, the
      respective Marker will only accept 1 value, and consider it required!

